  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You call forth a thick, ominous fog which fills a 15-foot radius sphere and echoes sounds of gnashing mandibles and snapping claws. When the fog appears, and the first time a creature enters the area on its turn or ends its turn there, a creature in the area must make a <strong>Wisdom saving throw</strong>. On a failed saving throw, the target takes <strong>4d6 psychic damage</strong> and its speed is reduced to 0 until the spell ends. An affected creature repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, taking <strong>2d6 psychic damage</strong> on a failure, or ending the spell on itself on a success.</p>",
